# Priority-queue load test. Three bulk batches on the SAME channel (email) so
# they contend for one per-channel rate-limit bucket. Submit order is low ->
# normal -> high; if the priority lanes work, the HIGH batch reaches `sent`
# first even though it arrived last. Each batch is 300 items (cap is 1000).
#
# Watch ordering by polling the three batch endpoints below, or:
#   watch -n1 'curl -s localhost:9090/metrics | grep nsys_delivery_attempts_total'
#
# Batch ids come back as {"batch_id": "..."}; paste each into its GET.

@host = http://localhost:8080

### low: POST 300 low-priority
# @name low
POST {{host}}/notifications
Content-Type: application/json

[
  {
    "recipient": "user-0@example.com",
    "channel": "email",
    "content": "low load item 0",
    "priority": "low"
  },
  {
    "recipient": "user-1@example.com",
    "channel": "email",
    "content": "low load item 1",
    "priority": "low"
  },
